node.text:
Here’s my quick step by step on how to swaddle your baby. Swaddling is the ancient technique that mimics the safety of being inside the womb & helps your baby sleep soundly. Whilst there’s almost nothing sweeter than a baby cocooned in it’s wrap, swaddling is used to help your baby feel calm and settled, keeping your baby warm & stops them from disturbing themselves. Babies often disturb themselves with their own startle reflex.  Swaddling prevents your baby from flailing her arms and legs, which can trigger the startle reflex. The warmth and light pressure of a stretch jersey wrap or muslin wrap aids sleep and that’s got to be a good thing! Save this video so you can refer to it when you need it 
#snugglehunnykids

Today I run through all the amazing functional features of our Growsuit all in onesies to have you ready for our release date Monday 19 April 8pm AEST. Here we go!
Sizing is Newborn 0000 to Size 1 (12-18 Months)
- Foldable hand mittens that open and close to keep baby’s hands in or open as a cuff
- All sizes have Foldable foot mittens that closes as a foot mitten/sock or open as a cuff. This means as your baby gets taller you can grow with your growsuit and get more use out of it
- The press studs and zipper are good quality YKK, the world standard in safety. Not only do we get these direct from YKK, they get safety tested by our own independent auditors also
- To open we have a long hidden lined zipper, ankle to ankle which means you can change a nappy without opening the chest up, chest stays covered, keeping baby asleep and chest warm. 
- The entire range is GOTS certified organic. This means from beginning to the end of production the entire process is organic. 
- All clothing garments come in a resealable bag to use as storage

node.text: Monday morning motivation for you ladies to dream big. Go after what sets your soul on fire and believe in yourself! Never in a million years did I ever imagine I would be standing in a warehouse of this size that will be the new home of Snuggle Hunny Kids. I started this journey when I was pregnant with Mason and I took 1 small step, created 6 products and thought I could design and create as a little hobby business selling baby products from my home to make mama and baby feel beautiful. Little did I realize how quickly we would grow our community and become the home for birth announcements and precious milestones. If you have been thinking of a career change or starting something new, don’t be overwhelmed with the task in front of you and just keep moving forward, no matter how small! Like I said I had never envisioned my business to be what it is today. It grew out of love, passion and creativity so organically I only have you to thank! I’ll keep you posted on the progress of our new HQ! Have a great week Mon x

Hold my hand daddy and show me the way
So that I can go out in the big world one day
Teach me the basics and then let me learn.
Should I ever get stuck I’ll know just where to turn . Cheer me up daddy when I’m feeling blue. I can always rely on a kind word from you. Dry my tears daddy when I’m feeling sad. A special mention to my husband, father to our 3 boys and business partner of Snuggle Hunny Kids. You will go to the end of the earth for our boys and they are so lucky to have you as their dad x
